{"id":238,"date":"2020-10-08T14:38:29","date_gmt":"2020-10-08T12:38:29","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/xanasoft.com\/?page_id=238"},"modified":"2023-04-29T07:36:50","modified_gmt":"2023-04-29T07:36:50","slug":"closedkeypath","status":"publish","type":"page","link":"https:\/\/sandboxie-plus.com\/sandboxie\/closedkeypath\/","title":{"rendered":"Closed Key Path"},"content":{"rendered":"<h1>Closed Key Path<\/h1>\n<p><em>ClosedKeyPath<\/em> is a sandbox setting in <a href=\"SandboxieIni\">Sandboxie Ini<\/a>. It specifies path patterns for which Sandboxie will deny <em>all<\/em> access by sandboxed programs, including <em>read<\/em> access. This setting essentially blocks registry keys from being accessed by sandboxed programs.<\/p>\n<p><a href=\"ProgramNamePrefix\">Program Name Prefix<\/a> may be specified.<\/p>\n<p>Example:<\/p>\n<pre><code>   .\n   .\n   .\n   [DefaultBox]\n   ClosedKeyPath=!msimn.exe,HKEY_CURRENT_USER\\Software\\Microsoft\\Internet Account Manager<\/code><\/pre>\n<p>The example blocks any program <em>other than<\/em> Outlook Express (<em>msimn.exe<\/em>) from accessing the registry key containing configured email accounts for the active user account.<\/p>\n<p>The value specified for <em>ClosedKeyPath<\/em> can include wildcards, although for registry keys, the use of wildcards is rarely needed. For more information on this, including examples that show the use of wildcards, see <a href=\"OpenFilePath\">OpenFilePath<\/a>. (<em>OpenFilePath<\/em> deals with files, not registry keys, but the principle of using wildcards remains the same.)<\/p>\n<p><strong>Note:<\/strong> <em>ClosedKeyPath<\/em> only blocks access to registry keys outside the sandbox, which have not yet been copied (or created) in the sandbox.<\/p>\n<p><strong>Note:<\/strong> Unlike the corresponding <a href=\"OpenKeyPath\">OpenKeyPath<\/a> setting, the <em>ClosedKeyPath<\/em> settings are always applied to programs in the sandbox, regardless of whether the program's executable file is inside or outside the sandbox.<\/p>\n<p>Related <a href=\"SandboxieControl\">Sandboxie Control<\/a> setting: <a href=\"ResourceAccessSettings#registry-access--blocked-access\">Sandbox Settings &gt; Resource Access &gt; Registry Access &gt; Blocked Access<\/a><\/p>\n<hr \/>\n<p>Go to <a href=\"SandboxieIni\">Sandboxie Ini<\/a>.<\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>Closed Key Path ClosedKeyPath is a sandbox setting in Sandboxie Ini. It specifies path patterns for which Sandboxie will deny all access by sandboxed programs, including read access. This setting essentially blocks registry keys from being accessed by sandboxed programs. Program Name Prefix may be specified. Example: . . . [DefaultBox] ClosedKeyPath=!msimn.exe,HKEY_CURRENT_USER\\Software\\Microsoft\\Internet Account Manager The &hellip; <a href=\"https:\/\/sandboxie-plus.com\/sandboxie\/closedkeypath\/\" class=\"more-link\">Continue reading <span class=\"screen-reader-text\">Closed Key Path<\/span> <span class=\"meta-nav\">&rarr;<\/span><\/a><\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":1,"featured_media":0,"parent":108,"menu_order":0,"comment_status":"closed","ping_status":"closed","template":"","meta":{"footnotes":""},"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/sandboxie-plus.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/pages\/238"}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/sandboxie-plus.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/pages"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/sandboxie-plus.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/page"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/sandboxie-plus.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/users\/1"}],"replies":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/sandboxie-plus.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/comments?post=238"}],"version-history":[{"count":2,"href":"https:\/\/sandboxie-plus.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/pages\/238\/revisions"}],"predecessor-version":[{"id":2285,"href":"https:\/\/sandboxie-plus.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/pages\/238\/revisions\/2285"}],"up":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/sandboxie-plus.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/pages\/108"}],"wp:attachment":[{"href":